title: Swisher ends up fifth in state meet
text:
Swisher ends up fifth in state meet STAFF REPORT sports@dancomnews.com Commercial-News.com 
CARMEL, Ind. — Seeger's Kiley Swisher ended her final IHSAA girls golf meet among the best in the state. 
Swisher shot 79 on Saturday at Prairie View Golf Club to end with a two-day total of 155, putting her in fifth place. 
With the No. 5 spot, Swisher made the All-State Team. 
PREP CROSS COUNTRY 
Danville competes at Peoria 
PEORIA — Carl Way took ninth with a time of 15 miuntes 19 seconds as the Vikings' boys team took seventh at the Peoria Central Invitational. 
William Powell was 41st for Danville (15:58), while Jeremiah Cooley was 61st (16:18), Phillip Hall was 70th (16:24) and Brandon Barfell was 74th (16:27). 
The Danville girls did not have a team score as Sadie Elliott was 16th (18:27), Dezerai Huckelberry was 85th (20:45), Shreja Patel was 94th (20:58) and Madison Smith was 146th (22:57). 
Danville wins at Oakwood 
OAKWOOD — Terry Dalton had a time of 17:50 for sixth place as the Danvile boys team won the team title at the Comet Classic. 
Sincere Williams-Davis was seventh (17:54) for Danville, while Easton Towen was eighth (17:59), Roberton Rangel was 15th (18:34) and Noah Hile took 25th (19:00). 
Chrisman was second with Kile McKee taking fifth (17:43) and Ben Brinkley taking ninth (18:01) while Oakwood/Armstrong-Potomac was fourth with Lucas Vasquez taking 12th (18:14) and Hoopeston Area was fifth with Trey Houmes taking second (17:10). 
In the girls race, Hoopeston Area was the only local team with a team score as they were third behind Heyworth and St. Thomas More. Gracie Eighner was third (21:05) to lead the Cornjerkers. 
PREP BOYS SOCCER 
HoopestoN Area 4, Iroquois West 2 
GILMAN — Skyler Barnard had two goals in the second half as the Cornjerkers beat Iroquois West. 
Nathan Michael had two assists for Hoopeston Area, while Nate Allison and Jonathon Linares each had one goal. 
The Cornjerkers are 14-5 and will face Judah Christian on Monday. 
Western Boone 3, Covington 2 
COVINGTON, Ind. — Logan Foster and AJ Kline each scored for the Trojans, but they would lose to the Stars at the Covington Invitational. 
Western Boone went on to defeat Faith Christian in the finals 2-1. 
Jansen Applegate had a assist for Covington, who is 11-3 and will start sectional play on Tuesday against Greencastle. 
PREP BOYS TENNIS 
Seeger 5, Benton Central 0 
VEEDERSBURG, Ind. — Borden Kennedy, Cal Stover and Coy Coffing each won in singles as the Patriots clinched an IHSAA Sectional title on Friday against the Bison. 
The doubles teams of Nick McGowen and Josh Orahood and Brock Bowlus and Logan Stout each had wins for Seeger, who is 15-5 and will play North Montgomery in a regional at Crawfordsville, Ind. 
PREP GIRLS TENNIS 
Danville 10th at duals 
BLOOMINGTON — The Vikings went 2-2 over the weekend to take 10th at the Bloomington Purple and Gold Duals. 
Danville defeated Springfield High 4-3 and Effingham St. Anthony 6-1 and lost to Normal University High 6-1 and Metamora 4-3. Lauren Ellis was 7-1 over the weekend while Emilee Wilson got the clinching win against Springfield High. 
PREP VOLLEYBALL 
Armstrong-Potomac takes third at Paris 
PARIS — The Trojans lost to Lawrenceville 25-19, 18-25, 15-11 but rebounded to beat Tuscola 25-19, 25-21 and Chrisman 25-21, 25-21 to take third at the Paris Tournament. 
Makenzie Vinson had 11 kills, 34 assists and 33 digs for Armstrong-Potomac for the day while Ashley Gayheart had 22 kills and 35 digs. 
The Trojans will play Westville on Tuesday. 
The Cardinals lost their first two games of the season. After beating Paris 25-18, 17-25, 15-9, they lost to West Vigo 25-20, 25-15, 15-12 before losing to Armstrong-Potomac. 
Hannah Eddy had 23 kills and five blocks for Chrisman, while Jordyn Lunger had 14 kills and 21 digs, Kodey Bush had 50 assists and Avoree Switzer had 32 digs. 
The Cardinals are 17-2 and will take on Milford on Tuesday. 
Hoopeston Area 2, Iroquois West 0 
HOOPESTON — Ashley Morgan had nine kills, two blocks and two digs as the Cornjerkers beat Iroquois West 25-18, 26-24. 
Annie South had two kills and two blocks for Hoopeston Area, while Jaida Wise ahd four aces and Lauren Sheppard had two aces and six digs. 
The Cornjerkers will play Oakwood on Tuesday. 
North Vermillion take second at BOW 
CAYUGA, Ind. — The Falcons beat Riverton Parke, but lost to Rockville in the title game of the Banks of the Wabash Tournament. 
North Vermillion will face Rockville again on Tuesday. 
JR. HIGH BASEBALL 
Hoopeston Area takes third in Class 2A 
EAST PEORIA — The Cornjerkers lost out to Bartonville Oak Grove West 4-0 in the third place game of the Class 2A IESA State Baseball Tournament. 
Hoopeston Area (18-2) lost earlier in the day in semifinal action to Teutopolis, who would go on to win the title with a 8-0 win over Joliet St. Raymond.
